<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10064b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10064b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10064b"> 64(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ch carrier pigeons / whistle in tail / to scare other birds</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le pigeon, ce joli petit animal si propre, si coquet, si s&eacute;duisant, est repr&eacute;sent&eacute; par sept types de <mark>pigeons-voyageurs</mark>. Les <mark>Chinois</mark> ont apport&eacute; un soin particulier &agrave; l&apos;&eacute;levage de ces beaux oiseaux et les pr&eacute;cautions qu&apos;ils prennent pour les prot&eacute;ger contre leurs ennemis sont tr&egrave;s curieuses &agrave; conna&icirc;tre. Ils portent, <mark>sur les plumes de la queue</mark>, un ou plusieurs petits morceaux de bambou juxtapos&eacute;s de fa&ccedil;ons diff&eacute;rentes et termin&eacute;s par un minuscule sifflet qui, pendant le vol de l&apos;oiseau, fait entendre un son plus ou moins aigu. Ce <mark>sifflement suffit, para&icirc;t-il, &agrave; &eacute;loigner des pigeons les oiseaux de proie fort nombreux en Chine</mark>. <font color="green">[The pigeon, this pretty animal, so clean, so trim, so alluring, is represented by seven types of carrier pigeon. The Chinese took special care in the breeding of these beautiful birds and the precautions they took in protecting them from their enemies are quite curious. On their tail-feathers they carry one or more small pieces of bamboo aligned in different ways and ending with a tiny whistle that, during the bird&apos;s flight, produces a more-or-less sharp sound. It seems that this whistle is enough to scare off the birds of prey so numerous in China.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 255(bis)</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01030l" href="c01all.htm#c01030l">VI.C.01:030(l)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
